This paper involves optimization algorithms applied to the Traveling Salesman Problem, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The use of ants as a crossover operator suggests the involvement of neural networks (cs.NE) or data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves the use of genetic algorithms (cs.LG) and data mining (cs.DM) to solve the problem.
